Speaking of the artifacts, what is going on with the Siva decorations along the walls of the Eastern Karana gorge.  When I was but a young lad, I insisted that that was Karana &quot;herself&quot; as a not-so-subtle nod to the restorer-destroyer role of Siva in Hindu mythos.  Turns out, Karana is a doddering old man according the amazingly uninspiring artwork in my handy and up-to-date Guide to Kunark.<br>
<br>
Whoops.  <br>
<br>
Since then, I've had to adjust my view of Karana to fit in more with the other gods... specifically Tunare.  If Tunare is the Mother of All, and Karana's blessing bring life to Norrath, putting two and two together makes Karana the likely consort of Tunare.  Therefore, when it rains, Karana is doing his part to fertilize his lover (not wife, lover)<br>
<br>
But Karana is also the Storm, wiping clean the slate of ALL creations, good and bad.  It doesn't add up to much in the end, as it'll all come full circle over and over and over.<br>
<br>
(Making the mental picture of a Faydark rainstorm more... graphic... in many ways)<br>
<br>
So, make yourself and others as comfortable as you can, make their short time here a pleasant as possible.  After all, there is no need for any concept of salvation or an everlasting Self... *NOTHING* can stand in the face of the Storm.<br>
<br>
Karana is the Duality<br>
Karana is the Tao<br>
Karana is Destruction<br>
Karana is Rebirth<br>
<br>
Pass through the Eye of the Storm to Know these things.<br>
<br>
(Yes, I watched far too many Kung Fu movies as a child.  My Kung-Fu DVD collection is a wonder to behold.<br>
<br>
