<br>
The biggest surprise to me was that Quellious is a little girl.  I somehow pictured her as being a more monkly figure.  Possibly the picture for Karana, even. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubanegrivm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banegrivm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 468<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/30/02 4:49:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2454.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> That isn't Karana...</span><hr size=1> Take a CLOSE look at those beings on the wall that you speak of. They are NOT Karana.<br>
<br>
You will find them up in Luclin outside the entry to the City of Shadows. They used to be on Norrath long ago.<br>
<br>
However, there was once a great war in the Rathe Mountain Passes between the gods when Rallos Zek tried to invade the plane of earth for the second time after his childer the ogres, were pushed back.<br>
<br>
All of the gods battled that day. Apart of that was a deep rivaly that goes between Solusek Ro the lord of flame and Luclin the godess of shadows. You'll notice there is &quot;Solusek's Eye&quot; and there is the &quot;Maiden's Eye&quot; up upon Luclin. Also note that you lose faction with Solusek Ro for killing in the Maiden's Eye. The Maiden's Eye was not always upon Luclin, why do you think there are so many ruins lying about? What was once on Luclin was once upon Norrath, hence the writings on the wall in the Eastern Karana Plains, nestled upon the wall within the chasm. <br>
<br>
One of those images on the left side leaving High Pass Hold, is Luclin herself, the maiden of shadow.<br>
<br>
From what I had managed to discover about EQ lore and the war, Solusek Ro despises Luclin partialy because she guards the prison of Rallos Zek and she also carries the book of Solusek Ro which is one of the three artifacts of the fourth hero of Trakanon's prophecy whi is ultimately to slay the Sleeper during a grand conjunction of the planes and heavens. (which in turn makes the opening storyline for EQ2).<br>
<br>
Solusek Ro felt it was cruel that Rallos Zek was made to watch the cursing of his children, and his response was to bend the dragonspine mountains which in turn brought the beating sun down upon what was then Tunaria, hence creating the desert of Ro, with the Oasis of Marr at its epicenter. For if the children of Rallos Zek were not going to be permitted to dwell upon Tunaria, then neither would any other.<br>
<br>
On a side note, I have my old Compendium (Codex of War) still backed up on my hard drive that details off this, including the beta documents that were guide handouts, along with all the screen captures that I took of important places. If anyone would ever like it, let me know. It is 17 meg's total (unzipped), and I will be more then happy to pass it along to anyone who wishes of it.<br>
<br>
